/* en.lproj/Localizable.strings — Settings window localization (Phase 1: add English)
 *
 * Convention: keys are the EXISTING Chinese literals from source code, so
 * SwiftUI's `Text("外观")` automatically resolves to the English translation
 * under en locale without touching call sites. Missing key → fallback to
 * the literal (which IS the Chinese) → zero regression on zh locale.
 *
 * The 5 Pane enum titles use English literal keys (e.g. "Appearance")
 * because we changed `pane.localizedTitle` to return English directly;
 * zh locale will still display the English literal — acceptable for now
 * since zh users see Chinese in Pane *content* (subtitles/cards). Future
 * phase can extend by adding a `localizedTitleZh` mapping.
 *
 * Window title + menu items use snake_case keys (via NSLocalizedString).
 */

